ul.li:
public GenericSelectQuery willPerformSelect(DataContext context, GenericSelectQuery query)


			Called from DataContext.performQuery(...) before running any select query, including prefetch queries. Implementation
			has a choice to modify an original query, replace it with alternative one, or return NULL, blocking query execution alltogether.

public boolean shouldMergeChanges(DataObject object, DataRow snapshotInStore)

			public boolean shouldProcessDelete(DataObject object)

			public void finishedMergeChanges(DataObject object)

			public void finishedProcessDelete(DataObject object)


			These methods are called by the ObjectStore whenever it performs an update of its state triggered by external
			events. Default ObjectStore behavior is to merge all changes to the existing objects, and change deleted objects state
			to TRANSIENT, removing them from the store. Delegate has an option to abort standard processing by returning "false" from
			"should*" methods.
